{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"16272","heading":"Reactor concepts research, development, demonstration, and commercial application","label":"16272 Reactor concepts research, development, demonstration, and commercial application","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch149/schIX/ptE","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2022—Subsec. (a)(2). , added par. (2). Former par. (2) redesignated (4).Pub. L. 117–167, § 10110(b)(2)Subsec. (a)(2)(A). substituted “shall evaluate the technical and economic feasibility of establishing and, if feasible, is authorized to establish” for “shall evaluate the technical and economic feasibility of the establishment of”.Pub. L. 117–263Subsec. (a)(4). , redesignated par. (2) as (4) and transferred it to appear after par. (3).Pub. L. 117–167, § 10110(b)(1)2020— amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to nuclear energy research programs.Pub. L. 116–2602018—Subsecs. (c) to (e). redesignated subsecs. (d) and (e) as (c) and (d), respectively, and struck out former subsec. (c) which related to establishment and administration of a Nuclear Power 2010 Program.Pub. L. 115–248"],"amendments":["Amendments2022—Subsec. (a)(2). , added par. (2). Former par. (2) redesignated (4).Pub. L. 117–167, § 10110(b)(2)Subsec. (a)(2)(A). substituted “shall evaluate the technical and economic feasibility of establishing and, if feasible, is authorized to establish” for “shall evaluate the technical and economic feasibility of the establishment of”.Pub. L. 117–263Subsec. (a)(4). , redesignated par. (2) as (4) and transferred it to appear after par. (3).Pub. L. 117–167, § 10110(b)(1)2020— amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to nuclear energy research programs.Pub. L. 116–2602018—Subsecs. (c) to (e). redesignated subsecs. (d) and (e) as (c) and (d), respectively, and struck out former subsec. (c) which related to establishment and administration of a Nuclear Power 2010 Program.Pub. L. 115–248"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Sustainability program for light water reactors","label":"a Sustainability program for light water reactors","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"reliability;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"capacity;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"component aging;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"safety;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"physical security and security costs;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"plant lifetime;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"operations and maintenance costs, including by utilizing risk-informed systems analysis;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"H","heading":null,"label":"H","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/H","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FH","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the ability for plants to operate flexibly;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"nuclear integrated energy system applications described in subsection (c);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"J","heading":null,"label":"J","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/J","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FJ","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"efficiency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"K","heading":null,"label":"K","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/K","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FK","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"environmental impacts; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"L","heading":null,"label":"L","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1/L","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F1%2FL","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"resilience.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Isotope demonstration evaluation","label":"2 Isotope demonstration evaluation","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 1 year after , the Secretary, acting through the Assistant Secretary for Nuclear Energy, shall evaluate the technical and economic feasibility of establishing and, if feasible, is authorized to establish an isotope demonstration subprogram of the program established under paragraph (1) to support the development and commercial demonstration of critical radioactive and stable isotope production in existing commercial nuclear power plants.August 9, 2022","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Consultation","label":"B Consultation","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary, acting through the Assistant Secretary for Nuclear Energy, shall consult with the Director of the Office of Science in carrying out the evaluation under subparagraph (A).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":"Definition of critical radioactive and stable isotope","label":"C Definition of critical radioactive and stable isotope","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this paragraph, the term “critical radioactive and stable isotope” has the meaning given the term in .section 18649(a) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Report","label":"3 Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall submit annually a public report to the Committee on Science, Space, and Technology of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Energy and Natural Resources of the Senate documenting funds spent under the program that describes program activities, objectives, and outcomes, including those that could benefit the entirety of the existing reactor fleet, such as with respect to aging management and related sustainability concerns, and identifying funds awarded to private entities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"4 Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There are authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary to carry out the program under this subsection $55,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2021 through 2025.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Advanced reactor technologies","label":"b Advanced reactor technologies","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall carry out a program of research, development, demonstration, and commercial application to support advanced reactor technologies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Requirements","label":"2 Requirements","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"are economically competitive with other electric power generation plants;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"have higher efficiency, lower cost, less environmental impacts, increased resilience, and improved safety;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"use fuels that are proliferation resistant and have reduced production of high-level waste per unit of output; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FA%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"use advanced instrumentation and monitoring systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"consult with the Nuclear Regulatory Commission on appropriate metrics to consider for the criteria specified in subparagraph (A);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"radiation fluence;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"temperature;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"pressure; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FC%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"corrosion;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"support research and development to aid in the qualification of advanced fuels, including fabrication techniques;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"support activities that address near-term challenges in modeling and simulation to enable accelerated design of and licensing of advanced nuclear reactors, including the identification of tools and methodologies for validating such modeling and simulation efforts;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop technologies, including technologies to manage, reduce, or reuse nuclear waste;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FG%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"currently operational research reactors at the National Laboratories and institutions of higher education;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FG%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"hot cell research facilities;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FG%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a versatile fast neutron source; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/G","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FG%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"advanced coolant testing facilities, including coolants such as lead, sodium, gas, and molten salt;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"H","heading":null,"label":"H","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/H","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FH","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"improve scientific understanding of nonlight water coolant physics and chemistry;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop advanced sensors and control systems, including the identification of tools and methodologies for validating such sensors and systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"J","heading":null,"label":"J","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/J","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FJ","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"investigate advanced manufacturing and advanced construction techniques and materials to reduce the cost of advanced nuclear reactors, including the use of digital twins and of strategies to implement project and construction management best practices, and study the effects of radiation and corrosion on materials created with these techniques;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"K","heading":null,"label":"K","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/K","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FK","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"consult with the Administrator of the National Nuclear Security Administration to integrate reactor safeguards and security into design;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"L","heading":null,"label":"L","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/L","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FL","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"support efforts to reduce any technical barriers that would prevent commercial application of advanced nuclear energy systems; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"M","heading":null,"label":"M","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2/M","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F2%2FM","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop various safety analyses and emergency preparedness and response methodologies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Coordination","label":"3 Coordination","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall coordinate with individuals engaged in the private sector and individuals who are experts in nuclear nonproliferation, environmental and public health and safety, and economics to advance the development of various designs of advanced nuclear reactors. In carrying out this paragraph, the Secretary shall convene an advisory committee of such individuals and such committee shall submit annually a report to the relevant committees of Congress with respect to the progress of the program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"4 Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16272/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16272%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There are authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary to carry out the program under this subsection $55,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2021 through 2025.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Nuclear integrated energy systems research, development, demonstration, and commercial application program","label":"c Nuclear integrated energy systems research, dev